Parliament, Tuesday, 17 November 2020 – The Portfolio Committee on Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs, (National Assembly), will tomorrow receive a briefing on the 2019-20 Annual Report by the Commission for the Promotion and Protection of the Rights of Cultural, Religious and Linguistic (CRL) Communities. Details of the virtual meeting are as follows: Date : Wednesday, 18 November 2020 Time: 09:00 – 13:00 Thereafter Portfolio Committee on Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs, will discuss the work of the CRL Rights Commission. Details of the virtual meeting are as follows: Date : Wednesday, 18 November 2020 Time: 19:00 – 22:00 Parliamentary committees are open to the media and the public. Journalists wishing to cover meetings (including receiving links to virtual meetings) should send their cellphone numbers to Mlindi Mpindi at mmpindi@parliament.gov.za for inclusion in the Parliamentary Communications Services WhatsApp Group, where such information is shared. Journalists must send these requests using their official email addresses (not private emails).
	
	Members of the public may follow sittings live on Parliament TV (DStv Channel 408), via live stream on Parliament YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
